oai_dc:dc.dc:description: First Presbyterian Church of Spring Hill
Color photograph of the ceiling of a historic church. The ceiling features an intricate design of tounge-and-groove panels creating an interesting geometrical design.

The original building used by the First Presbyterian Church of Spring Hill was built in 1844. The current building was built in 1888 and cost $4,000. The building was constructed in the vernacular eclectic style of architecture.
